{
  "texts": [
    "In the field of Natural Language Processing, Named Entity Recognition (NER) is not a new notion.",
    "Since its introduction by the MUC-6 in 1995, it has been a subtask of Information Extraction with substantial research reported.",
    "Named Entities (NEs) are textual items of interest with people, organisations, locations, and numbers being common examples.",
    "The aim of NER is to recognise and categorise different types of named entities in a structured or unstructured text.",
    "This domain has attracted a lot of interest."
  ]
}